## Before Shipping Checklist

Use this checklist before creating a PR or marking a feature complete:

### Concurrency
- [ ] Reviewed all `async def` functions for shared state access
- [ ] All dictionaries/sets that could be modified concurrently have lock protection
- [ ] No locks held during I/O operations (use copy pattern)

### Initialization & Null Safety
- [ ] All global/module-level variables checked for `None` before access
- [ ] Exception handlers (especially disconnect/cleanup) handle `None` gracefully
- [ ] Early-lifecycle code (startup, first request) has `None` guards

### Data Consistency
- [ ] API request/response formats reviewed for consistency
- [ ] No mixing of prefixed/unprefixed identifiers
- [ ] Field names consistent across endpoints
- [ ] Database schema matches API format

### Testing
- [ ] Unit tests pass non-trivially (verify with actual data)
- [ ] Edge cases tested (None state, empty collections, concurrent access)
- [ ] Integration tests receive and process real data

